<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="281" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[728,1325,685,1108]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[734,889,685,714]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Satunin, 1903" authorityName="Satunin" authorityYear="1903" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cricelulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roborovskii">Cricelulus roborovskii Satunin, 1903</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="2" pageNumber="281">Upper part of Shargol’dzhin River, Nan Shan, Qinghai, China.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="281" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[728,1325,685,1108]" lastBlockId="2.[120,1325,1114,2250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">
Analysis of mtDNA demonstrated basal position of P. roborouskii in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1910" box="[1195,1319,838,871]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phodopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Phodopus</taxonomicName>
. Within P. roborouskii, there are two distinct mtDNA clades: main clade in most parts of the distribution and eastern clade in Jilin Province, China. Populations of the main clade are characterized by high intraspecific genetic polymorphism in the absence of pronounced geographical structuring. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="281" type="synonymic_list">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" targetBox="[816,820,2225,2250]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[120,1325,1114,2250]" box="[122,522,1157,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[122,522,1157,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[120,1325,1114,2250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicName authority=": Satunin, 1903" authorityName=": Satunin" authorityYear="1903" box="[122,519,1197,1226]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phodopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="roborouskii" subSpecies="roborovski">P.r.roborovski:Satunin,1903—Russia(STuva),NW&amp;SMongolia,andChina(NE&amp;SXinjiang,Gansu,Qinghai,InnerMongolia[=NeiMongol],Ningxia,NShaanxi,NShanxi,andNHebei).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[120,1325,1114,2250]" box="[122,1277,1319,1344]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicName authority="Mori, 1930" authorityName="Mori" authorityYear="1930" box="[122,487,1319,1344]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phodopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="roborouskii" subSpecies="praedilectus">P.r.praedilectusMori,1930—China(EInnerMongolia,NWJilin,andNLiaoning).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[120,1325,1114,2250]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicName authority="Vorontsov &amp; Kryukova, 1969" authorityName="Vorontsov &amp; Kryukova" authorityYear="1969" box="[122,719,1354,1383]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phodopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="roborouskii" subSpecies="przewalski">P. r. przewalski Vorontsov &amp; Kryukova, 1969</taxonomicName>
— Kazakhstan (E part of Zaysan Depression in East Kazakhstan Region) and China (NW Xinjiang).
</paragraph>
</caption>
